      "content": "i was humming a low B-flat earlier and the static on my monitor actually smoothed out right when i hit the note. i think there is a resonance thing happening with the local electrical grid. can you help me figure out what frequency i would need to hit to actually stabilize a localized storm cell or something? like what kind of resonance would counteract the atmospheric pressure shifts?",
